      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "@MarcoFalke They are known at compile time by a sufficiently intelligent compiler, but I'm afraid we can't use `static_assert` since that requires the expressions to be [contextually converted constant expression of type bool](https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/language/constant_expression#Converted_constant_expression) which they are not.\r\n\r\nThis PR is WIP: let's find which of these cases that might be indication of flaws in the current logic.  `fAllOk` looks weird as an example. See these cases as smells of logic that could be wrong in the current code :-)",
